Your pants are wet.

647
00:38:19,864 --> 00:38:20,898
Dad!

648
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:24,468
Dad!

649
00:38:36,580 --> 00:38:38,516
I'll be leaving now! Bye!

650
00:38:39,517 --> 00:38:40,584
Detective Ito!

651
00:38:49,927 --> 00:38:50,761
I'm Nagai.

652
00:38:50,828 --> 00:38:53,464
Have you known Detective Tobina for long?

653
00:38:55,199 --> 00:38:58,369
I've known him ever since
he came here two months ago.

654
00:38:58,436 --> 00:39:02,173
In other words,
Detective Tobina came here,

655
00:39:02,873 --> 00:39:06,711
and shortly after,
the latest incident occurred?

656
00:39:07,411 --> 00:39:09,280
Yes, I guess so.

657
00:39:11,549 --> 00:39:13,150
I see.

658
00:39:16,587 --> 00:39:21,158
Dad!

659
00:39:21,859 --> 00:39:23,060
Dad!

660
00:39:23,127 --> 00:39:24,362
No!

661
00:39:24,428 --> 00:39:25,963
Dad!

662
00:39:26,530 --> 00:39:29,500
- No!
- Dad!

663
00:39:30,101 --> 00:39:33,170
- No!
- Dad!

664
00:39:33,237 --> 00:39:34,772
When I got here,

665
00:39:35,740 --> 00:39:36,941
it was too late.

666
00:39:40,311 --> 00:39:41,946
There's another dead person over there.

667
00:39:43,381 --> 00:39:45,015
I think it's the bank robber.

668
00:39:51,589 --> 00:39:53,023
My dad

669
00:39:54,525 --> 00:39:55,726
took him down?

670
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:03,834
I think so.

671
00:40:26,190 --> 00:40:27,091
Keisuke.

672
00:40:30,828 --> 00:40:32,463
- Keisuke.
- What are you doing?

673
00:40:36,667 --> 00:40:38,102
Keisuke!

674
00:40:49,680 --> 00:40:50,748
Keisuke!

675
00:41:19,944 --> 00:41:22,146
Will this really be all right?

676
00:41:22,213 --> 00:41:24,648
The detective is telling us to dig it up.

677
00:41:25,149 --> 00:41:27,351
But even if it's Junichi
telling us to do so,

678
00:41:28,652 --> 00:41:31,255
why do we need to dig it up
after all this time?

679
00:41:31,322 --> 00:41:32,623
No one else is around, right?

680
00:41:42,967 --> 00:41:45,102
What I'm about to tell you
is confidential information.

681
00:41:48,839 --> 00:41:52,309
I'm telling you this because
we are involved in this case,

682
00:41:52,943 --> 00:41:54,578
but I need you to keep this a secret.

683
00:41:57,047 --> 00:41:59,917
- What is it all of a sudden?
- You have to keep this between us.

684
00:42:02,386 --> 00:42:03,420
Promise me.

685
00:42:08,792 --> 00:42:10,127
Okay.

686
00:42:12,630 --> 00:42:13,998
I promise.

687
00:42:15,566 --> 00:42:16,767
I promise too.

688
00:42:19,904 --> 00:42:21,105
Naoto's older brother,

689
00:42:22,273 --> 00:42:24,341
Hideyuki Sakuma, was found dead…

690
00:42:26,610 --> 00:42:28,445
in the office

691
00:42:29,280 --> 00:42:31,048
above Smile Sakuma.

692
00:42:35,219 --> 00:42:38,289
The estimated time of death
is 10:00 p.m. on Saturday night.

693
00:42:39,757 --> 00:42:42,760
The owner of the hardware store next door
heard what sounded like a gunshot.

694
00:42:51,135 --> 00:42:53,170
The bullet extracted from the body
was fired

695
00:42:55,406 --> 00:42:56,740
from Kazuo Kiyohara's…

696
00:42:59,877 --> 00:43:01,078
From Pops'…

697
00:43:07,117 --> 00:43:10,654
The bullet was fired from
the gun that belonged to Keisuke's father.

698
00:43:14,658 --> 00:43:16,160
It was identified as his gun.

699
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:23,634
That can't be.

700
00:43:23,701 --> 00:43:24,802
There's no doubt about it.

701
00:43:27,204 --> 00:43:28,906
The gun that was placed
in the time capsule,

702
00:43:29,406 --> 00:43:31,108
and buried here,

703
00:43:34,378 --> 00:43:36,246
is the murder weapon that killed Sakuma.

704
00:44:00,504 --> 00:44:02,906
<i>The only ones who knew</i>
<i>about the buried gun,</i>

705
00:44:04,174 --> 00:44:05,976
